This paper deals with approximation algorithms for constraint satisfaction problems, which are a fundamental topic in theoretical computer science. The paper presents a randomized polynomial-time approximation algorithm for k-CSPd, which is a generalization of the boolean MAX k-CSP2 problem. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories of arXiv CS, including cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.CG (computational geometry), and cs.LG (machine learning).
